{
  "stem": "2539.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my father's friends used to come and-- men, and they used to discuss politics and stuff like that.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So this I remember vividly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I don't-- I don't think they were so terribly social, going to nightclubs and stuff like that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They went a few times.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But it was a rarity more than a-- than a routine [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] activity.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can't tell you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I know that we were felt-- of course, we never felt fully as a full citizen, never.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was always the threat that someone might come.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I-- I-- I didn't ponder over it, strange enough.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We didn't-- we took it for granted that we are different, that we are a minority, that we-- that we're supposed to suffer for being a minority, for being Jewish.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But somehow or other-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] well, I had Polish friends, of course.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I had a lot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In fact, the police-- the-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the headquarters of the police were two houses away from-- from us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the commander's daughter, Hanka, went to the same class as I.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I lived practically in the-- in the commander's or the chief of police's house with Hanka and she came to our place.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, I mean, that was one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there was Vanda and there was this one, I mean, the girlfriends constantly-- the Polish girlfriends, Christian girlfriends, because I went to school with them.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that was a natural thing that we mix together.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But of course, on the side, I had Jewish girlfriends, also the ones that went to the high school.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "People somehow or other stuck-- the children stuck to the schools they went to.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
